article.headline: Saint Joseph's 80, Rhode Island 69
article.story: KINGSTON, R.I. -- Carl Jones scored 28 points and Saint Joseph's shot 60.9 percent in the second half to rally for an 80-69 victory over Rhode Island in an Atlantic 10 Conference game on Wednesday night. After trailing 38-36 at halftime, the Hawks (17-10, 7-5) made 14 of 23 shots in the second half, which they began with a 21-5 run. Jones scored nine points during the run, which put Saint Joseph's ahead 57-43 with 11:59 remaining. The Rams (5-22, 2-10) shot just 34.3 percent (12 of 35) in the second half as they lost their fourth consecutive game. C.J. Aiken finished with 18 points and Langston Galloway 16 for Saint Joseph's. Galloway, who ranked 10th in the nation in 3-point percentage at 45.2 percent, made 4 of 7 behind the arc. Orion Outerbridge scored 19 points for Rhode Island, and Jonathan Holton had 11 points and nine rebounds.
